Cause + Result

We can use different expressions to show that one action was the reason for another action.

I was late because the train was delayed.
(Result : I was late)
(Reason : the train was delayed)

The train was delayed, so I was late.

The train was delayed. Therefore, I was late.
(Reason : the train was delayed)
(Result : I was late)

We can use as a result of followed by the noun; as a result/the reason why followed by the clause.

As a result of the delayed train, I was late.

The train was delayed and as a result, I was late.

The delayed train was the reason why I was late.
